<item>
            <title>[HIVE-6189] Support top level union all statements</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-6189</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve always wondered why union all has to be in subqueries in hive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After looking at it, problems are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hive Parser:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Union happens at the wrong place (insert ... select ... union all select ...) is parsed as (insert select) union select.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are many rewrite rules in the parser to force any query into the a from - insert -select form. No doubt for historical reasons.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Plan generation/semantic analysis assumes top level &quot;TOK_QUERY&quot; and not top level &quot;TOK_UNION&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The rewrite rules don&apos;t work when we move the &quot;UNION ALL&quot; into the select statements. However, it&apos;s not hard to do that in code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
