                            <comment id="13872426" author="hagleitn" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2014 18:58:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=leftylev&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;leftylev&quot;&gt;leftylev&lt;/a&gt; - the documentation in the link you sent looks good. We could specify that unions can be used in views, insert, and ctas statements, but this I&apos;m thinking that&apos;s almost self explanatory. As for hive .12 and below - the restriction was that unions could only be used within a subquery. I.e.: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;select_statement union all select_statement union all ...&quot; had to be written as &quot;select * from (select_statement union all select_statement union all ...) unionresult&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ditto for CTAS, insert, create/alter view as.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does that make sense?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
